Roasted Pear and Kabocha Squash with Pumpkin Seeds

Pickled Squash
1 kabocha squash (~3lbs) halved
1 c white wine vinegar
kosher salt

Remove and discard the seeds from the squash. Quarter each halve and set aside 3 quarters to roast. Using a mandoline, slice the remaining quarter of squash paper thing and place in a heatproof container. In a small saucepan over high heat, heat the vinegar. Pour the vinegar over the squash, then season with salt and let cool to room temp.

Roasted Squash and Pear
3/4 reserved kabocha
2 red pears, cored and cut into 6 wedges
6 tbsp olive oil divided
6 thyme sprigs divided
kosher salt to taste

Preheat oven to 475F. Line 2 rimmed baking sheets with parchment paper. Cute the remaining squash quarters into 1" pieces. Place the squash on one baking sheet and the pear on the other. Drizzle each baking sheet with 3 tbsp of olive oil and sprinkle each with 3 thyme sprigs. Season wach with sall and toss. Roast the squash and the pears in the oven until brown and tender, 18-20 min for the squash and 8-10 min for the pears. Remove from the oven and discard the thyme.

For Serving
1 red pear, thinly sliced
2 tbsp fresh lemon juice
1 tbsp pumpkin seed oil
1 tsp finely grated lemon zest
1/2 c toasted pumpkin seeds
grated parmesan

Gently toss the warm roasted squash, roasted pears and raw pears with the lemon juice, pumpkin seed oil, lemon zest and pumpkin seeds. Taste and adjust the seasoning with salt as needed. To serve, arrange the roasted squash and pears on a platter along with the pickled squash, then top with grated parmesan.
